<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2018/06/06/spring-cloud-skipper-1-0-5-released">Spring Cloud Skipper 1.0.5 released</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/5cffed9a3aad16d33d07f6e7ef2ebbb7?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/mpollack">Mark Pollack</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2018-06-06 19:54:20.101">June 6, 2018</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="3294" href="/blog/2018/06/06/spring-cloud-skipper-1-0-5-released#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><div class="paragraph">
<p>On behalf of the team, I am pleased to announce the release of Spring Cloud Skipper 1.0.5 GA</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Skipper is a lightweight tool that allows you to discover Spring Boot applications and manage their lifecycle on multiple Cloud Platforms. You can use Skipper standalone or integrate it with Continuous Integration pipelines to help implement the practice of Continuous Deployment.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The <a href="https://docs.spring.io/spring-cloud-skipper/docs/1.0.5.RELEASE/reference/htmlsingle/#getting-started">getting started section</a> in the reference guide is the best place to start kicking the tires.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>This is primarily a bug fix release. Significant changes since the 1.0 GA release are:</p>
</div>
</div>
</section>
